Prior to Sacramento State: Played two seasons at Saddleback JC in Mission Viejo, Calif…appeared in all 11 regular season games for the Gauchos in 2013…finished the year with 54 tackles…also added 6.0 tackles-for-loss, recovered a fumble and had an interception…was credited with at least one tackle in each game and had a career high 11 against Santa Ana…added seven stops at Orange Coast and against Golden West…was limited to six games as a freshman where he had nine total tackles, including a pair of sacks. High School: A 2012 graduate of Oak Ridge HS…earned all-Delta League honors as a senior after recording 103 total tackles…posted a career high 15 stops (including 11 solos) against Del Oro…had 11 total tackles against Cordova and Granite Bay. Personal: Majoring in criminal justice…parents are Jim and Shirley BoisD'Enghien.}
